    source: "WEG40100 The Planets Collection p.203",
    summary: "Carosi XII is one of the few planets to openly support the New Republic. Originally a frozen ice ball, it was terraformed over decades after the sun Carosi expanded into a red giant and devoured the inner five planets including the Carosite homeworld (Carosi IV). The Carosites are gentle, furry bipeds (1.3-1.7m) with extraordinary medical talents — their first aid skill starts at 5D and they gain +2D brawling when protecting patients. They operate the Sudden Restoration, a galaxy-roaming hospital ship providing free medical care. The Carosites refuse to install cybernetic enhancements (prosthetics only). Hot springs in crystalline caves grant an extra healing roll per day after 2 hours of soaking. A hidden New Republic outpost (8 X-wings, 8 Y-wings, 208 personnel) is built into a mountainside.",
    locations: "Newlife Point (only city, built on first refugee landing site, still expanding). Avuae Sea (only surface water body, mineral-rich, never freezes, marine life). Hot Springs (crystalline caves, volcanic-heated, +1 extra healing roll/day after 2hr soak). New Republic Outpost (secret, mountainside, 8 X-wings + 8 Y-wings + 5 airspeeders + 4 shuttles, 208 personnel). Carosite hospitals and cybernetics fitting centers.",
    ofNote: "Carosites: furry bipeds, first aid 5D automatic, +2D brawling protecting patients/helpless. Reproduce only twice in lifetime (litters of 1-6). Lifespan 120 years. Verbal promises completely binding. Medical droids reprogrammed at half cost on Carosi XII. Sudden Restoration: modified Kuat Class C Frigate hospital ship (330m, 220 crew + 380 medical, 2 X-wing escorts). Hot Springs: +1 extra natural healing roll/day. Refuse cybernetic enhancements — prosthetics only. Medical metaphors pervade language. 'The Preventers' faction advocates aggressive anti-Imperial action. Rinacats: mountain predators (PER 5D, tireless trackers, can go 1 month without water). Bars heavily taxed — dietary advice given constantly by everyone."
