    summary: "Miser is the innermost planet of the Bespin system, a small metal-rich world built around a large iron and gententhium core. All the metals used to construct Cloud City were mined from Miser; the surface still bears the scars of that massive effort. Its proximity to the sun, lack of atmosphere, and slow rotation create lethal surface conditions — the dayside bakes to 530 standard degrees, the nightside cools to -210. Environment suits can operate on the dayside for only 30–45 minutes before heat overload. During Cloud City's construction, life support systems were installed in the tunnels to allow Ugnaught mining crews to work; those systems are long gone. The planet's metal core generates a powerful magnetic field that renders all but heavily shielded equipment useless; comlink range averages only six meters, varying from static to a kilometer at random. The surface is dotted with deep craters that served as landing bays during the Ugnaught operation. The tunnels still contain heavy machinery — obsolete but occasionally valuable for parts — and are infested with mynocks feasting on raw ore and solar radiation.",
