    source: "WEG40125 Galaxy Guide 3: The Empire Strikes Back p.9",
    summary: "Hoth is the sixth planet from a blue-white star of the same name. The inner five planets are lifeless, and the only remaining orbit is occupied by a wide, chaotic asteroid belt whose debris causes heavy meteor activity on the planet. Hoth's axial tilt, orbital position, and atmospheric makeup combine to produce subzero temperatures at all times — daytime highs hover around -32 degrees standard, while nights plunge to -60 degrees or colder with windchill. The entire surface is covered in ice. Volcanic fissures open steam vents in various locations, depositing rock and minerals in darker patches on the glacier plains; a few mountain chains penetrate the permanent ice shelves, some of which are geologically active. In Hoth's southern hemisphere, a massive ocean churns beneath the pressure of ice; tidal pulls from Hoth's three nameless moons create fissures in the ice layers, sending jets of ocean water into the freezing air where they freeze into spires of ice. Primitive ocean algae is suspended in these columns and glaciers, and a species of annelids called ice worms carve through the ice to feed on the algae. Along Hoth's equator is a deep fissure in the ice shelves reaching hundreds of meters into permanent shadow — never exposed to the sun — where a cache of lumni-spice grows, a rare fungal growth valued by the galaxy's criminal element. Lieutenant Commander Luke Skywalker first discovered Hoth after the Alliance fled the Yavin system, crashing on the frozen world after his ship was caught in the hyperstream of a trans-dimensional cometary body.",
    locations: "Echo Base (northern hemisphere, former Alliance base of operations — now abandoned). Equatorial fissure (lumni-spice cache, guarded by a dragon-slug). Southern ice ocean (accessible through fissures). Glacier plains (wampa cave territories).",
