    source: "REUP Star Wars RPG: Revised Expanded Updated p.469",
    summary: "Corellia is a Core World famous for producing a people as sentimental as they are reckless, fiercely loyal to the philosophy of 'Corellia for Corellians' and notorious for their independence from central galactic authority. The Corellian system is believed to have been assembled by the enigmatic Celestials, who arranged five worlds — Corellia, Drall, Talus, Tralus, and Selonia — around the star Corell using buried planetary repulsors and the hyperspace engine Centerpoint Station. Corellia's Humans may themselves have been transplanted by the Celestials. By 30,000 BBY the system was part of the Rakatan Infinite Empire. The Corellians later perfected the modern hyperdrive by 25,000 BBY. Corellia kept its surface largely rural by moving starship construction facilities into orbit, and the capital Coronet became a lively hub for spacers and traders. King Berethron e Solo abolished the monarchy in 312 BBY. Under the Empire, a Diktat administered the system under Imperial supervision. After the Battle of Endor, the rival Grand Admirals Pitta and Grunger destroyed each other fighting over the system. Corellia joined the New Republic but retained fierce independence, and in 16 ABY Thrackan Sal-Solo triggered the Corellian Insurrection, attempting secession and using Centerpoint Station as a superweapon. Sal-Solo resurfaced again during the Second Corellian Insurrection at 40 ABY, pushing the system into civil war with the Galactic Alliance.",
    locations: "Coronet (capital city; eclectic bazaar for spacers and bargain-hunters). Centerpoint Station (ancient Celestial-built hyperspace engine suspended between Talus and Tralus; capable of destroying distant stars with repulsor blasts). Drall (fellow Corellian system world; native Drall species). Selonia (fellow Corellian system world; native Selonian species). Talus and Tralus (double worlds orbiting each other in the Corellian system).",
    ofNote: "The Corellian system is uniquely engineered — five inhabited worlds plus Centerpoint Station in a single star system, all assembled by the Celestials. Centerpoint Station has served as both a hyperspace engine and a superweapon (used by Thrackan Sal-Solo in 16 ABY to destroy stars). Corellia is the premier starship-building world in the galaxy; the Corellian Engineering Corporation (CEC) produces most of the galaxy's light freighters and bulk transports. Han Solo and Wedge Antilles are both Corellian. Corellian CorSec (Corellian Security Force) maintains local law enforcement. The system has a long history of attempted secession from whatever central authority exists. Home of the Corellian Merchants' Guild (CMG) — one of the largest private trade organizations in the galaxy. Membership open to all native-born Corellians and crew of Corellian ships. The Empire views it as a hive of anti-Imperial activity but cannot shut it down without dire economic consequences; individual Guildhouses are completely autonomous, so closing one just spawns another. Provides trade contacts, repair bays, legal aid, backup finance, and a free inter-Guildhouse message service. Also hosts a branch campus of the Institute of Starship Engineers (ISE)."
