    majorImports: "Technology, foodstuffs, starship parts",
    source: "WEG40069 Galaxy Guide 7: Mos Eisley",
    summary: "Mos Eisley is the largest spaceport city on Tatooine, famously described as a 'wretched hive of scum and villainy.' Despite its rough reputation, it serves as the planet's primary hub for interstellar trade, legitimate and otherwise. The city is administered by Imperial Prefect Eugene Talmont, who reports to Governor Tour Aryon in Bestine. Law enforcement is handled by Lieutenant Harburik's police force and a detachment of about 20 stormtroopers. In practice, Jabba the Hutt's influence overshadows Imperial authority — his contacts in local government and with the sector Moff enable him to protect his smuggling operations and keep the stormtroopers unaware of the true scale of illegal activity.",
    locations: "Docking Bay 94 (operated by the De Maal family; six docking bays total plus eight warehouses). Spaceport Customs (customs inspection facility). Spaceport Speeders (repair shop southeast of Docking Bay 94; vehicle and starship maintenance). Mos Eisley Cantina (Chalmun's Cantina). Jabba's Townhouse (Hutt crime lord's city residence with guard barracks and garage). Lup's General Store (Lup's Wares and Supplies; provisions, equipment, and discreet illegal transactions). Jawa Traders (droid shop run by Aguilae and Mace Windu the Squib). Heff's Souvenirs (junk shop and forgery front run by Mopiin Jarron). Kayson's Weapon Shop (personal armaments dealer; black market weapons available). Militia Building (headquarters for up to 50 militia members and stormtrooper garrison). Docking Bay 92 (Dom Antyll's repair bay; best starship mechanic in Mos Eisley). Dockside Cafe (spacer bar adjacent to Docking Bay 92; hiring spot for smugglers). Spaceport Hotel (40 rooms, 15 credits/night; no-questions-asked Sullustan clerk). Spaceport Control Tower (Sienar Observation Module; five stories; operated by J9-5 droid and two Human technicians). Lucky Despot Hotel (Valarian's hotel and criminal front; 40 staff, rival to Jabba). Zygian's Banking Concern (branch office/pawn shop; triple-lined vault with 200-300K credits on deposit; 15% loan rate; staffed by Sylvet Depp, Debrelle, and manager Giwers). Police Station (20 full-time officers; rooftop landing pad; newer section of city). Train Depot (p.74-75; rail service with schedule connecting Mos Eisley to outlying settlements). The Cutting Edge Clinic (Dr. Evazan operating under alias 'Dr. Cornelius'; cyborging clinic with high failure rate). Dim-U Monastery (p.76-78; runs a BoSS ship transponder forgery service). Notsub Shipping Company (largest company on Tatooine; ~1,000 employees; northern edge of city; CEO Armanda Durkin secretly pirates as 'the Duchess'). Bestine (imperial capital, seat of Governor Tour Aryon).",
    ofNote: "Mos Eisley is the primary destination for most visitors to Tatooine. Docking fees, customs bribes, and warehouse storage are the economic lifeblood of the city. The police patrol on foot, scooter, and Dewback. Spaceport Customs inspectors like Putten Beatus are notoriously corrupt and demanding. Smuggling is pervasive but carefully concealed from the Imperial garrison."
