    majorImports: "Technology, tools, foodstuffs",
    source: "WEG40124 Galaxy Guide 1: A New Hope (Wayfar scenario)",
    summary: "Wayfar is a small, isolated moisture farming settlement on Tatooine, located south of Mos Eisley roughly on the route toward Tosche Station. Home to approximately 500 residents, it is governed by the retired farmer Mayor Kaimer. The town scrapes by on moisture farming and the occasional trade caravan passing through the desert. Its isolation makes it vulnerable — Tusken Raiders, desert worms, and roving criminal elements are constant threats. The settlement has a skyhopper hangar run by Karl Mott, a motel operated by Camelle, and a population of tough, independent farmers who will fight to protect their community when pushed.",
    locations: "Mayor Kaimer's office. Karl Mott's skyhopper hangar. Camelle's motel (edge of town). Moisture farms (surrounding area).",
    ofNote: "Approximately 275 of Wayfar's 500 residents are capable of bearing arms, though none have combat experience. The settlement sits in territory prowled by desert worms — massive 20–50 meter burrowing predators with STR 11D and teeth dealing 15D damage. Notable residents: Mayor Kaimer, Jahn Tanner and his son Shan, sharpshooter Ran Padell, nurse-turned-innkeeper Camelle, mechanic Karl Mott."
