    government: "None",
    techLevel: "None",
    majorExports: "None",
    majorImports: "None",
    aliases: ["Yavin IV"],
    source: "REUP Star Wars RPG: Revised Expanded Updated p.473",
    summary: "Yavin 4 is a jungle moon in an unremarkable Outer Rim system far from major space lanes, yet it has been a pivotal site in galactic history multiple times. Its dense surface is blanketed by enormous Massassi trees with great crowning branches, supporting climbing ferns, nebula orchids, and thick blueleaf shrub mulch. Fauna includes woolamanders, whisper birds, anglers, piranha-beetles, runyips, and strange creatures descended from ancient Sith experiments. The moon was first settled by the Sith Lord Naga Sadow and his Massassi warriors. The renegade Exar Kun was later chased here; the Jedi burned off much of the jungle in an orbital bombardment and subsequently installed a subterranean terraforming station. The Jedi then erased the moon from star charts. Hyperspace scouts of the Hydian Way rediscovered the system; it briefly saw a rush for Corusca gemstones found in the atmosphere of the gas giant Yavin. During the Galactic Civil War, Rebels from Dantooine established a base in the abandoned Great Temple of the Massassi. Tracked by the Death Star, the Rebels launched a desperate fighter assault and Luke Skywalker destroyed the battle station. After a long abandonment, Skywalker returned to establish a Jedi academy. The Yuuzhan Vong later colonized it as a Shaper caste installation; Jedi Anakin Solo helped redeem a Shamed One there, inadvertently giving rise to the Jeedai cult that would help undermine the Vong invasion.",
    locations: "Great Temple of the Massassi (Level A: launch bays, hangar lift platforms; Levels B & C: command center, war room, computer processing, briefing rooms, barracks, storage; Level D: ancient throne room with skylights — left unmodified by the Alliance). Massassi Ruins (scattered pyramidal structures throughout the jungle). Temple of Exar Kun (site connected to the spirit of Exar Kun; source of Jedi trials during the New Jedi Order era).",
    ofNote: "Site of the Battle of Yavin (0 BBY) — the Rebel X-wing assault that destroyed the first Death Star; this battle defines the BBY/ABY dating system used across the galaxy. No permanent population; no starport — just a cleared landing field. The gas giant Yavin itself hosts atmospheric lifeforms — see the Yavin entry.\n\nJedi Praxeum (11 ABY): Luke Skywalker established a Jedi academy in the Great Temple, training a new generation of Jedi Knights for the New Republic. Jedi training exercises from Jedi Master Vo'ren Faalo's 'Book of Practical Lightsaber Technique' include: Five lightsaber cadences of escalating difficulty — 1st cadence: evaporate ball bearings atop wax cylinders (19 cylinders at 10° intervals, Heroic lightsaber/Moderate control/Moderate sense); 2nd: 72 cylinders at 5° intervals, 360° coverage, ~3 seconds per strike; 3rd: 180 cylinders at 2° intervals, 1/3 second per strike with complex mathematical patterns; 4th: 360 cylinders at 1° intervals with simultaneous complex calculations; 5th (Jedi Master level): no physical cylinders — the Jedi knows where they would be, concluding with telekinetic lightsaber control (Heroic +60 telekinesis). Remote training: deflect stun bolts back at a hovering globe (2D-6D stunner/dodge, 1D-3D stun damage). Telekinesis exercises: rolling marbles up hemispheres with precise Force control, stacking billiard balls into free-floating structures. The Oxygen Bottle: extract pure oxygen from air into a sealed bottle using only telekinesis (Heroic+ rolls). Dark Side Points increase all training difficulties by +5 per point — cadences can serve as a gauge of Dark Side corruption. New Force Powers: Instinctive Astrogation Control (control-based alternative to sense-based version), Sense Path (vision of whether current actions lead to the Dark Side), Feed on Dark Side (Dark Jedi gain Force Points from others' anger — automatic Dark Side Point).\n\nFlora with game effects — Blueleaf shrub: +2 to all Perception rolls for 1 hour; Moderate stamina roll at end or suffer exhaustion; second dose within a day requires Difficult stamina. Massassi-blossom tea: substitute medpac on sick/wounded with Moderate first aid roll. Climbing fern rhizomes: Moderate difficulty to cut; supports Human weight; fresh resin is waterproof adhesive when cured. Nebula orchid pods: edible nutrient paste; ~1 liter flammable oil per pod. Touch-not shrub: contact = wound-level rash; water spreads resin; Mon Calamari double healing time; dissolves organic fabric. Grenade fungi: explodes on contact — 3D+2 spore cloud damage; chain-detonates nearby fungi; can be harvested as improvised grenades.\n\nFauna in creature lookup: Crawlfish (good eating, leads to water), Yavinian Runyip (head butt STR+1D; carries 130–150 kg; hide resists touch-not), Woolamander (territorial, early-warning system, raids camps), Stintaril (aggressive scavenger, swarms at dawn/dusk)."
