    majorExports: "None",
    majorImports: "None",
    aliases: ["Yavin Thirteen"],
    source: "WEG40119 Galaxy Guide 2: Yavin and Bespin p.26–29",
    summary: "Yavin 13 is a desert moon of the great gas giant Yavin, and one of the most ecologically diverse desert worlds in the system despite its harsh conditions. Little topsoil remains — constant winds strip it away, leaving only bare rock, mesas, and shifting sand. A large ocean fills much of the southern hemisphere, and fierce fog storms regularly drift across the surface but dissipate almost as quickly as they form. The dramatic temperature swing between day (up to 15 GST) and near-freezing nights means most lifeforms are highly adapted for extremes. Towering cacti up to 16 meters tall form dense forests, storing water in spongy tissues and sending deep roots into the rocky floor. Shorter-lived plants like the korin flower and saldi bush bloom and die within a single brief growing season. A wide variety of insect life forms the foundation of the food chain. Two sapient species share the moon: the nomadic, limbless reptilian Slith, who travel in small family groups and hunt at night using venomous fangs; and the Gerbs, small social beings with huge heat-radiating ears who have built permanent underground burrow settlements and developed primitive agriculture and irrigation. The two species rarely interact.",
    locations: "Southern ocean (source of moisture and fog storms). Cacti forests (major ecological zones; Slith shelter here during day). Rocky plains and mesas (Gerb settlement sites; Tripion habitat). Underground Gerb burrows (adobe-linked, family-based communities with irrigation canals).",
    ofNote: "Neither the Slith nor the Gerbs have had significant contact with the Empire or the Alliance. Both are centuries from industrialization without outside intervention. Slith cannot speak galactic Basic — they communicate by rasping scales across surfaces; some sounds carry distinct emotional character (haunting, beautiful, frightening).\n\nCreatures in the Creature Lookup: Twilight Lizard (small crepuscular lizard; excellent water/food source, valuable trade good with the Slith), Burning Snake (absorbs solar heat; radiates 4D heat damage waves; danger multiplies in groups), Tripion (scorpion-like with 3 venomous tails and seizing pincers; 600+ species logged; 1–18m)."
