    majorExports: "Corusca gems",
    majorImports: "Supplies, equipment, crew",
    source: "WEG40119 Galaxy Guide 2: Yavin and Bespin p.30–32",
    summary: "Damarind Corporation constructed a large space station in orbit above Yavin, positioned midway between the gas giant and its first moon. The station is not in geosynchronous orbit — it roams and tracks the cyclonic storms in Yavin's atmosphere, since it is in and around these storms that the larger corusca stones may be harvested. The station serves as the fishing port for a company fleet of specially designed sturdy trawlers that descend into Yavin's atmosphere. Each trawler carries a crew of 12, up to eight one-man skiff vessels, and a five-kilometer-long energy purse seine — a mesh net that traps solid matter in the atmosphere while letting gases pass. Skiffs deploy in an arc behind the trawler, monitoring the energy pulses of the seine; any resistance change indicates a catch. When something is detected, the skiffs close the seine's purse strings and the catch is retrieved. A fishing cruise lasts 10 Standard Days. Company-employed crews receive a wage plus a percentage of profits; independent trawler crews receive nothing from Damarind if they return empty — a failed cruise can mean loss of the vessel and years of menial work at the station to save passage home. Despite the risks, independent corusca fishermen continue to brave Yavin's atmosphere each cycle, chasing the elusive big catch. Several experimental vessels attempting to go deeper into the atmosphere have never returned; Damarind offers a standing reward for technology that can survive the deeper pressure zones.",
    locations: "Docking bays (company and occasional licensed visitors). Station pub and entertainment center (Damarind subcontractors). Wegsphere court. Trawler fleet berths.",
    ofNote: "Access: legitimate visitors occasionally permitted to dock for a substantial fee. Security is extremely high — all personnel and cargo are searched on departure without exception, including visiting company security inspectors. Docking fee: 100 credits/day (free for company vessels). Imperial and local customs patrol.\n\nNPCs: Typical Corusca Fisherman (DEX 3D+2, MEC 3D+2, space transports 4D+2, value 3D, stamina 3D+2; Character Points 3). Damarind Station Security (DEX 3D, blaster 5D+1, dodge 4D+2, search 7D, STR 3D; blaster rifle 5D, blast vest +1 energy/+1D physical).\n\nHazard: Floater sharks and floater squids are attracted to the energy pulses of the seines and regularly attack skiffs and trawlers. A floater caught in a seine thrashes violently, endangering both vessels and crew."
