    source: "WEG40119 Galaxy Guide 2: Yavin and Bespin p.34",
    summary: "Following the destruction of the Death Star at the Battle of Yavin, the Empire established an orbital salvage station to recover, catalog, and analyze the wreckage. In the immediate aftermath, other salvagers — including the Ugors — arrived and carted off large chunks of debris before an Imperial cordon was established. The station operates under the command of Major Reskik of the Imperial Security Bureau, supported by three squadrons of TIE fighters (including six bombers) and a full battalion of stormtroopers with a heavy weapons unit. The salvage team consists primarily of civilian engineers from the major defense contractors who designed the Death Star's primary systems, assisted by military zero-G work crews. Engineers aim to identify every design weakness for incorporation into any future battle station. Space skiffs and individual flying suits are used to approach debris; each piece is cataloged by scanning computer, moved by repulsor loadlifter, and transported to the station by cargo shuttle for examination, decontamination, and analysis. Reskik has ordered the operation to proceed slowly and carefully to maintain the appearance of a peaceful civilian mission as long as possible.",
