    source: "WEG40095 Galaxy Guide 6: Tramp Freighters p.49",
    summary: "Adarlon is a rugged, mountainous world whose Human inhabitants are obsessed with pleasure and entertainment. Its three major cities lie along the west coast of the northern continent on a narrow plateau between mountains and sea. One of the first colonies settled in this region of space, Adarlon was created by decree of the Old Republic Senate, selected for its beauty rather than natural resources. The early settlers — many from Alderaan — pioneered the holo industry and the planet became the home of the galaxy's best entertainers. Though its prominence has declined under the Empire, underground holos depicting the Empire unfavorably are fueling a new era of cinematic creativity. The planet features elaborate total-immersion theme parks where guests carry out live-action adventures with actors, droids, and holos. Despite its glamour, a strange malaise has fallen over the population as the people hide from the horror of the Empire in their entertainments.",
    locations: "Three major cities on western coast of northern continent (200+ years old, grid-pattern streets now converted to lush parkland). Adarlon Spaceport (Imperial Consulate, Customs inspectors, 100 stormtroopers). City of Balderdash (connected to spaceport by whisper-transit). Multiple theme parks offering total-immersion amusements. Forested regions between mountains and seas (temperate, wet). Climate-controlled cities (rain only in early mornings).",
