    summary: "Karideph is one of the most wildly overpopulated planets in the galaxy — essentially one giant city inhabited by the Kari, an insect-like hive species standing approximately one meter tall. The surface is covered by endless rows of carefully tilled gardens with no wilderness remaining. Enormous cities with pressurized upper floors dot the surface, but most Kari live underground in tunnel systems criss-crossing the planet, some dug as deep as 12 kilometers. The Kari are a true hive society: alone, an individual Kari is little more than an animal, but together they form an advanced group consciousness. They communicate through a complicated series of clicks and whistles, with 'singers' gathering and passing information between Hatches (family groups of 20-30). The best singers, called 'bards,' broadcast to the entire planet and comprise the leadership structure.",
    locations: "Capital City (surrounds the spaceport, immense towers). Tunnel systems criss-crossing the planet (up to 12 km deep). Imperial enclave around the spaceport. University of Universal Thought (founded by alien scholars studying the Kari group mind). Endless surface gardens covering every centimeter of land, including terraced mountainsides.",
    ofNote: "The Empire has refused to allow the Kari to develop or purchase space technology, fearing their tremendous birth rate could spread them across the galaxy. 200 stormtroopers patrol the Imperial enclave. Virtually impossible to enter or leave spaceport without rigorous search. Navigating the tunnels requires hiring a Kari guide (20 cr) or an entire Hatch (80+ cr) to push through the crowds. One of the Cluster's economic hubs, importing staggering amounts of raw materials and foodstuffs. A faction of Hatches secretly collaborates with the Empire in exchange for technology. The worst Kari insult: a screech meaning 'You take up too much room!'"
