    summary: "The Mestra system contains one of the largest asteroid fields in the galaxy — no planets remain, all destroyed in some ancient war. An estimated 100 trillion sizable chunks of rock fill the system, hundreds the size of small moons, many rich with durelium ore essential for hyperdrive construction. The system is controlled by the Minos-Mestra Corporation, formerly owned by VernanGroup but now run by local investors purely for short-term profits. Most miners are freelancers in name but indentured servants in practice, as the corporation monopolizes all ore purchases, vital goods, and services. Legends speak of ancient alien artifacts of immense value found in asteroid caves — 'the big haul' that every miner dreams of.",
    locations: "Javis 12 (egg-shaped asteroid, ~400 km across, on belt outskirts — only starport, company headquarters, landing beacon, repair/refuel at 200% list price). Mining 'burgs' spread through the trans-orbital belt. Private asteroids owned by wealthy mining families near Javis 12, featuring ornate palaces. Company smelting ships ('poundies') that pulverize asteroids to extract minerals.",
