    summary: "Pergitor was once a lush tropical garden planet and thriving mining world, established by the Jesa Corporation as its major training and research center. Nearly a century ago, a deep bore mining project caused an enormous volcanic eruption that covered the planet in ash for years and permanently tainted the atmosphere with pollutants. The resulting scandal destroyed Jesa Corporation and devastated the economy. Now gas masks must be worn at all times outside and all buildings must be airtight. The planet's history has swung between rigid conservatism and brief liberalization — 30 years ago the youth rebelled against the repressive society, but 15 years later the Church of Infinite Perception staged a revolution, overthrew the liberal government, exiled the royal family, and established a fundamentalist theocracy strongly supported by the Empire.",
    locations: "Starport (600 stormtroopers stationed). Temples of the Church of Infinite Perception (weekly mandatory group confessions). Volcanic mining regions (extremely rare mineral deposits). Merchant homes (trade agreements finalized over late afternoon meals).",
    ofNote: "State crimes read to every arriving crew — violations can bring summary execution: (1) All drugs and medication strictly forbidden, (2) Paranormal abilities (the Force) illegal, (3) No public entertainment — singing, holos, jokes, even laughing in public, (4) No luxury goods imports including jewelry or precious metals, (5) Sacrilege against the Church is capital. Church inspectors search ships after Imperial inspectors — belongings frequently stolen or damaged. The Church itself is the largest black market operator, secretly importing luxuries for its own hierarchy. The Pergitor Resistance (former liberalization leaders) operates in hiding. Weekly mandatory confessions make secrets nearly impossible to keep. The Empire recruits heavily from Pergitor's youth for the Imperial Navy."
