    summary: "Travnin is a desolate, wind-swept moon circling a gas giant — the only planet in its double-star system. The terrain is extremely rugged and nearly barren of life. It serves as the Imperial administrative hub for the Minos Cluster, housing the regional offices of the Empire, the HQ for the Imperial Fleet of the Cluster, and the residence of the reclusive Moff. The Human population exists solely because of the Imperial base, brought in long ago to manage galactic affairs. Nearly everyone works for the Empire as clerks, stevedores, navy personnel, or entertainers. The planet has been in dire straits as the Empire reduces its presence in the Cluster, with nearly one-third of the population losing their jobs. The natives are corrupt and servile to their superiors, terrified of the Empire they serve, and nearly universally disliked across the Cluster.",
