    summary: "Bimmisaari specializes in 'fur and moving plants.' Waving asaari trees cover the world's surface, constantly swaying even when no wind blows — they can move their leafy branches of their own accord, though their roots are firmly anchored. The planet's intelligent inhabitants, the Bimms, are governed by a planetary council whose members are referred to as Law Elders. The planet had been a nominal member of the Old Republic but withdrew when the galactic government became too corrupt for the Bimms' tastes. Far from the Core and considered mostly useless, the planet was left alone by the Empire and escaped most of the tyranny inflicted on the rest of the galaxy. Since the Battle of Endor, Bimmisaari has become a favorite stopover for shoppers from all over the galaxy, and the New Republic is determined to set up relations and an alliance with the world.",
    locations: "Tower of Law (meeting place for the planetary council; fairly modest building connected to a taller marketplace; rooms filled with wall-size tapestries decorated with scenes from the Bimms' favorite stories; upper levels converted into a museum with items dating back to the middle era of the Old Republic). Marketplace (three-level dome without sides and just a hint of a roof, reflecting the Bimms' preference for open air; roof extends to cover the dome framework in bad weather; has existed in one form or another for over two hundred years; always crowded with yellow-clad Bimms haggling and shopping).",
    ofNote: "Bimms love to shop and haggle. Since becoming a major center of trade post-Endor, the council of Bimmisaari is just now opening negotiations to join the New Republic. During a diplomatic mission to Bimmisaari, Princess Leia Organa Solo and her party were ambushed by an unknown species of attackers later identified as the Noghri."
