    summary: "Dolomar is the only planet orbiting its star. Originally a colony world of the Republic, it was settled after a rich discovery of ores and specialized minerals and crystals. After the Battle of Endor, Dolomar quickly allied with the New Republic, but Grand Admiral Thrawn's campaign of conquest subjected the world to bitter and desperate fighting. The colonists live underground in immense caverns and tunnels that protect them from both the extreme cold and orbital bombardments. The surface consists of nothing more than glaciers, snowdrifts, and ice-shrouded mountains.",
    locations: "Diflu (largest underground complex; hidden amongst the caverns and tunnels of the L'tiri Peaks, the northernmost mountain chain; hosts shops, space vessel repair facilities, and cantinas). L'tiri Peaks (northernmost mountain chain housing Diflu and other underground settlements). Underground Caverns and Tunnels (interconnected subterranean cities where the colonists live).",
    ofNote: "The colonists are extremely resilient and stubborn. When the Empire attacked, the initial Imperial invasion fleet was ambushed and wiped out. Currently, Imperial warships are attempting to gain a permanent foothold in the system, but Dolomar's defense fleet is holding its own thanks to New Republic support. The Empire has conducted limited ground attacks and orbital bombardments hoping to penetrate planetary shield generators. Dolomar's gunners have shot down most Imperial landing transports — only a small number of troops have landed. Those ground forces that reach the underground cities are eliminated in fierce street fighting, as the local inhabitants know the streets and alleyways infinitely better than Imperial Army troops."
